This paper focuses on modeling and analyzing the temporal performance variations experienced by a mobile user in a wireless network, which is a common topic in the field of computer networks (cs.NI). The paper also discusses the impact of these variations on system-level design, which falls under the category of control and optimization (cs.SY). The analysis involves stochastic geometry and queueing theory, which are both topics in information theory (cs.IT). The paper also evaluates the system-level Quality of Service (QoS), which is a topic in machine learning and artificial intelligence (cs.MA). Finally, the paper discusses the performance of mobile devices streaming video and downloading large files, which falls under the category of multimedia (cs.MM).
